nordlicht (0.3.5+git20141105.4345819-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * build from upstream Git snapshot 4345819, changelog summary:
    - move libpopt dependency from the library to the tool
    - add more detailed licensing information
    - seek to the beginning of the file for each track
    - allow the specification of a multi-track layout in API and CLI
    - introduce options 'start' and 'end' to set the range in the video
      nordlicht will work on
    - mpv lua script tweaks:
      . separate styles for small and large nordlicht
      . start fullscreen after 0.1 sec.
      . add zoomed-in barcode
    - cache some information about the video
    - add new barcode styles:
      . "column": take each frame's middlemost column
      . "thumbnails": draw thumbnails in regular intervals
      . "slitscan": take single columns, constantly moving one column per
        frame to the right and wrapping back to the left (experimental)
      . "volume": draw volume level
    - small bug fixes, cleanup and refactoring
  * make d/copyright machine-readable, as per DEP-5
  * bump Standards-Version to 3.9.6, no changes needed

 -- Roland Hieber <rohieb@rohieb.name>  Thu, 06 Nov 2014 22:38:30 +0100

nordlicht (0.3.5+git20140703.31723cf-1) UNRELEASED; urgency=medium

  * import upstream Git snapshot 31723cf:
    - Introduce nordlicht_error(), which returns a description of the last error
    - Move display of "Building keyframe index..." to the tool
    - Add a --quiet switch to the tool, that suppresses progress output
    - CMake: Check if help2man is installed at configure phase
    - On Windows, use _fullpath() instead of realpath()
    - Move most of the README to http://nordlicht.github.io/
    - Remove PNGs from the repository
    - Use avg_frame_rate instead of r_frame_rate

 -- Roland Hieber <rohieb@rohieb.name>  Thu, 03 Jul 2014 18:08:37 +0200

